==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Stenostome
<hw>Sten"o*stome</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>steno`s</grk> narrow, little + <grk>sto`ma</grk> mouth.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Having a small or narrow mouth; -- said of
certain small ground snakes (<fam>Opoterodonta</fam>), which are unable
to dilate their jaws.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stent</ent>⟦br⟧
